                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="307823" author="adilger" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 08:53:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I enabled OAL on to see if I could use it for tracking hot object IO on the OSTs with a user script instead of via lamigo, but wasn&apos;t able to turn OAL off afterward.  I think having a simple way to aggregate data from OAL for this would be useful for debugging but it should be possible to turn it off again once that is finished.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="307722" author="jhammond" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 13:41:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was designed in to make it faster. Under the original implementation there were no shared locks between readers and writers. I guess it could be done under the semaphore we added but what is the use case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
